text: Man, Lattice/Karn is a shitshow
It sure is
It just drags games out
That last one on MOC closed fast enough
MOC?
Magic Online Championship
Live now
Just had two Lattice locks in three games
What're they playing?
Lattice/Karn is one of those combos that makes folks thinks they've invented fire and showing the world how clever they are...
People don't just scoop to the lock?
Also, tangentially related: I've been cutting Swansong because it doesn't hit artifacts. Has anyone else had this problem?
The lock doesn't win by itself.
Screw you if you play it without a wincon.
(not you personally, <@U3QMCLQQG>)
I've been trading it out for Delay, Arcane Denial or Negate; whichever the deck was missing previously.
I'm not scared of most artifacts in Varina, but rather wraths, etc. so swan song stays in.
Henry, you can't cast spells unless you have passive mana production like Blinkmoth Urn. If you have no creatures, you've lost.
I haven't lost until you've reduced my life to 0.
Yes I'm a petty prick about it
You've chosen this path, follow it through.
I have better things to do than sit at a game that I'm locked out of for 20 minutes while twiddle dum grinds out a win.
I do too, but I'm also petty enough to waste their time too.
I guess?
If they put the lock in, they have a wincon. It's just a matter of how long it takes them to get there. :face_with_rolling_eyes:
Then they can show it.
If they tell me they have a win in the deck, I'll let them look for it and reveal it and scoop.
I fully recognize it's illogical and petty on my part, but that is the hill I've chosen to die on.
I'm finding these walker-based decks pretty dull to watch
Like anime,walkers were a mistake
Lol! What?
Not really, walkers are fine-ish
And even if this standard winds up being a trash fire it was an interesting experiment which I respect
This standard is really weird.
They don't make for a particularly interesting viewing experience, and I think they lead to dull games at the amateur standard level, but that's a tricky thing to balance
Very slow, but also very powerful
I do think we need more answers to walkers
But again, they can only have so many answers in standard at once
There are a few okay ones in the set. Despark and Spark Harvest, along with direct damage spells, but yeah, even with all that it's a bit dicey.
If they can land 3 or 4 walkers it really becomes a catch-22 between attacking the walkers and attacking them.
Esp in this set with so many low to the ground ones
Elderspell too, but yeah, finite answers
Yeah. And a bunch of them protect themselves. Kasmina, Tibalt, Teyo, Vraska, Angrath...
Which can make swinging at 2-4 walkers so unproductive it's just not worth it to try.
I'm not sure what to think of it yet.
Like I said, even if it's a mess I respect them trying crazy stuff
The only way to get radical successes is to risk radical failures
Sure - I have no problem with them trying this, but I hope they don't continue down the path of considering exile just another zone.
Kaya's Ghostform, too
new eldrazi preprocessors and postprocessors
That's sorta in flavor for the Eldrazi, and the way they did it was very tame.
Take it to Blogatog
The problem such as it is with processors is it's such a tame effect to violate that space for it seems weird
